to call yourself a victim?

786
00:52:43.076 --> 00:52:44.077
Victims?

787
00:52:45.370 --> 00:52:47.372
What about the parents

788
00:52:47.455 --> 00:52:51.376
who lost their life savings and home
and even quit their jobs

789
00:52:52.460 --> 00:52:54.087
because of their kid's gambling?

790
00:52:56.590 --> 00:53:00.510
What about the father who's slapped
in public by someone half his age…

791
00:53:03.013 --> 00:53:05.724
<i>but still has to kneel and beg.</i>
<i>all because of his kid?</i>

792
00:53:11.313 --> 00:53:13.815
What about the mother
who scrubs greasy grills

793
00:53:13.899 --> 00:53:15.609
in the kitchen of a barbecue joint

794
00:53:15.692 --> 00:53:18.028
<i>because the father can't do anything else</i>

795
00:53:19.112 --> 00:53:20.113
<i>but watch their kid?</i>

796
00:53:25.911 --> 00:53:29.998
What about the father
who goes from the police to the ERPB.

797
00:53:30.498 --> 00:53:36.171
even while being looked down on
and treated like some peddler.

798
00:53:36.254 --> 00:53:40.383
begging and crying for his child
to be saved?

799
00:53:48.808 --> 00:53:49.768
Victims?

800
00:53:53.063 --> 00:53:55.106
They're the real victims.

801
00:54:01.446 --> 00:54:04.741
You had countless chances to stop.

802
00:54:06.076 --> 00:54:08.787
And you're the ones
who threw those chances away.

803
00:54:13.500 --> 00:54:17.545
Do you really want to quit gambling
and be forgiven by the people around you?

804
00:54:18.880 --> 00:54:20.840
Then admit you are perpetrators.

805
00:54:23.301 --> 00:54:25.887
Never stop reflecting on yourselves

806
00:54:27.138 --> 00:54:28.890
and never stop asking for forgiveness.

807
00:54:32.560 --> 00:54:34.521
This is your last chance.

808
00:55:01.589 --> 00:55:02.924
Here you go.

809
00:55:03.883 --> 00:55:05.302
It's hot. isn't it?

810
00:55:08.179 --> 00:55:09.139
Oscillate.

811
00:55:12.183 --> 00:55:14.352
You earn money through labor.

812
00:55:14.436 --> 00:55:16.730
There's no such thing
as a get-rich-quick scheme.

813
00:55:17.772 --> 00:55:19.816
Keep scrubbing.

814
00:55:19.899 --> 00:55:22.068
-Scrub your minds clean.
-You need more suds.

815
00:55:22.652 --> 00:55:23.820
Hand it over.

816
00:55:26.740 --> 00:55:28.491
That's it. Good.

817
00:55:30.869 --> 00:55:36.624
That means you now have
98.320.000 won left to pay your parents.

818
00:55:36.708 --> 00:55:38.960
You clean up your own mess.

819
00:55:39.044 --> 00:55:40.462
Oh. and…

820
00:55:43.256 --> 00:55:45.592
<i>To page. press one. To record a message…</i>

821
00:55:47.719 --> 00:55:48.678
Your pagers.

822
00:55:49.262 --> 00:55:50.096
4868253.

823
00:55:50.180 --> 00:55:51.723
Do you remember what this means?

824
00:55:51.806 --> 00:55:53.058
"I love you. Come quickly."

825
00:55:53.892 --> 00:55:54.726
Love you.

826
00:55:54.809 --> 00:55:58.063
Please give our phones back now.
We'll only make calls.

827
00:55:58.146 --> 00:56:00.231
What high schooler
would use this nowadays?

828
00:56:00.315 --> 00:56:03.151
Freedom is only granted
when you take responsibility.

829
00:56:03.234 --> 00:56:04.778
And most importantly.

830
00:56:05.362 --> 00:56:07.155
I don't believe a gambler's word.

831
00:56:07.864 --> 00:56:09.032
I'll page you.

832
00:56:10.158 --> 00:56:11.951
337337.

833
00:56:12.452 --> 00:56:14.537
Oh man.

834
00:56:17.207 --> 00:56:18.249
It's really fine.

835
00:56:18.333 --> 00:56:21.503
After all. I'm the reason
your phone is broken.

836
00:56:21.586 --> 00:56:25.173
It's just the screen that's broken.
It's still usable.

837
00:56:27.258 --> 00:56:28.343
I just feel bad.

838
00:56:29.010 --> 00:56:31.846
I said I'd protect you. but I failed.

839
00:56:31.930 --> 00:56:33.390
So please. okay?

840
00:56:33.473 --> 00:56:36.059
Just pick one.
There are so many phones here.

841
00:56:36.142 --> 00:56:37.644
-Which is the latest?
-It's fine.

842
00:56:37.727 --> 00:56:38.561
Come on. pick one.

843
00:56:38.645 --> 00:56:39.979
-What's the latest--
-Oh?

844
00:56:41.231 --> 00:56:43.900
Then I'll just take a quick look.

845
00:56:45.068 --> 00:56:46.903
-Do you know this one?
-Yes.

846
00:56:46.986 --> 00:56:51.074
They changed the CPU on this model.
so the Internet should be really fast.

847
00:56:51.157 --> 00:56:52.242
-It's so cool.
-I see.

848
00:56:52.325 --> 00:56:53.159
Look.

849
00:56:53.243 --> 00:56:54.285
Right.

850
00:57:15.598 --> 00:57:17.225
Sir. can I please get a flip phone?

851
00:57:17.308 --> 00:57:19.102
-No. we don't need one.
-A flip phone.

852
00:57:19.769 --> 00:57:21.062
I'm not the addictive type.

853
00:57:21.146 --> 00:57:22.188
-Not anymore.
-Hello?

854
00:57:22.272 --> 00:57:24.858
-I'm bringing another addict. sir.
-I'm not an addict.

855
00:57:24.941 --> 00:57:26.192
-Sir. I'm not…
-Yes. sir.

856
00:57:26.276 --> 00:57:27.444
Goodbye.

857
00:57:27.527 --> 00:57:28.653
-Hwang Gi-tae!
-Hello.

858
00:57:28.736 --> 00:57:29.946
One. two.

859
00:57:30.029 --> 00:57:34.742
Hwang Gi-tae!

860
00:57:34.826 --> 00:57:36.703
-Your shop is…
-Life is so tough.

861
00:57:36.786 --> 00:57:37.704
-Here.
-Thank you.

862
00:57:37.787 --> 00:57:38.746
<i>In the latest poll.</i>

863
00:57:38.830 --> 00:57:42.375
<i>Minister Choi Gang-seok</i>
<i>surpassed 50% approval for the first time.</i>

864
00:57:42.459 --> 00:57:46.337
<i>outpacing opposition leader Hwang Gi-tae</i>
<i>by 17%.</i>

865
00:57:46.421 --> 00:57:49.632
<i>Whether Minister Choi Gang-seok</i>
<i>will enter the presidential race…</i>

866
00:57:49.716 --> 00:57:52.051
-Well. then.
-Please look out for us.

867
00:57:52.135 --> 00:57:52.969
Thank you.

868
00:57:53.052 --> 00:57:54.262
This way. please.

869
00:57:54.345 --> 00:57:56.347
-Thank you for treating us. sir.
-Thank you.

870
00:57:56.973 --> 00:57:58.141
All right.

871
00:57:59.225 --> 00:58:01.102
I see you're already out campaigning.

872
00:58:02.103 --> 00:58:04.147
-Choi Gang-seok?
-Choi Gang-seok?

873
00:58:04.230 --> 00:58:05.857
-Why is he here?
-Have a seat.

874
00:58:05.940 --> 00:58:07.358
I'm a regular here. Great food.

875
00:58:08.359 --> 00:58:10.737
Ma'am. can I get another <i>tang </i>here?

876
00:58:10.820 --> 00:58:12.947
Just a moment. please.

877
00:58:24.834 --> 00:58:28.713
Why are you visiting the markets
before even registering as a candidate?

878
00:58:29.380 --> 00:58:31.799
Isn't that something you do
while campaigning?

879
00:58:32.300 --> 00:58:34.844
-This looks delicious.
-Yes. it's good.

880
00:58:36.346 --> 00:58:38.181
Minister Choi Gang-seok. have you heard?

881
00:58:38.264 --> 00:58:39.390
Oh. right.

882
00:58:40.308 --> 00:58:42.727
People don't really hear
the things said about them.

883
00:58:45.480 --> 00:58:47.857
I heard rumors in Yeouido.

884
00:58:49.651 --> 00:58:52.445
You're using your dead daughter
to make a run for president.

885
00:58:53.738 --> 00:58:55.907
They say politics is heartless.

886
00:59:10.296 --> 00:59:12.340
You're all ears when it's about others.

887
00:59:12.924 --> 00:59:16.010
I hear the Mirae Daehan Party
is holding an emergency meeting today.

888
00:59:18.221 --> 00:59:19.681
I guess you weren't told.

889
00:59:20.181 --> 00:59:22.225
I wonder what they need to discuss

890
00:59:23.476 --> 00:59:25.478
that they didn't tell you about.

891
00:59:28.940 --> 00:59:31.776
Could they be planning
to replace their presidential candidate

892
00:59:31.859 --> 00:59:34.696
because your approval ratings
are dropping?

893
00:59:39.742 --> 00:59:41.119
<i>Whose idea was this?</i>

894
00:59:41.202 --> 00:59:43.413
I'll head over
to the conference room right now.

895
00:59:45.081 --> 00:59:47.709
I'm the Mirae Daehan Party leader!

896
00:59:47.792 --> 00:59:49.210
Who's going to stop me?

897
00:59:51.296 --> 00:59:52.297
What is it?

898
00:59:54.424 --> 00:59:56.092
Sir. you have a visitor.

899
00:59:56.175 --> 00:59:58.219
Do I look like I want company right now?

900
00:59:58.803 --> 01:00:01.014
He has something to tell you
about the ERPB.

901
01:02:07.765 --> 01:02:10.727
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim

902
